cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with information theory and cryptography, which suggests that it belongs to cs.IT and cs.CR. The focus on coding theory and the use of the Lee metric suggest that it could also belong to cs.CC. The mention of key size and complexity suggests that it could belong to cs.DS. Finally, the mention of Galois rings suggests that it could belong to cs.SI.
